+# False Positive Analysis: CVE-2026-1526 and CVE-2026-2229 in undici v5.28.5
+
+## Summary
+
+**CVE-2026-1526 and CVE-2026-2229 do not affect undici v5.28.5.**
+
+Both CVEs require the `permessage-deflate` WebSocket compression extension, which
+was never implemented in the v5 release line. Scanner findings against v5.28.5
+for either CVE are false positives.
+
+---
+
+## CVE Overview
+
+| CVE ID          | GHSA ID              | Description                                      |
+|-----------------|----------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
+| CVE-2026-1526   | GHSA-vrm6-8vpv-qv8q  | Unbounded permessage-deflate decompression (DoS) |
+| CVE-2026-2229   | GHSA-v9p9-hfj2-hcw8  | Invalid server_max_window_bits crashes process   |
+
+| Field              | Value                                                      |
+|--------------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
+| Package            | npm: `undici`                                              |
+| **Affected range** | `< 6.24.0` AND `>= 7.0.0, < 7.24.0`                      |
+| **Patched in**     | v6.24.0, v7.24.0                                           |
+
+---
+
+## Why v5.28.5 Is Not Affected
+
+### Reason 1: permessage-deflate was never implemented in v5
+
+The permessage-deflate extension was introduced in undici v6.18.0 (commit
+`5a564bd9`). The v5 release line never received this feature.
+
+```bash
+git ls-tree -r v5.28.5 --name-only | grep -i "permessage\|deflate"
+# (no output)
+```
+
+There is no `permessage-deflate.js`, no `isValidClientWindowBits()`, and no
+`createInflateRaw()` call in v5.28.5.
+
+### Reason 2: Sec-WebSocket-Extensions header is disabled
+
+In v5.28.5, `lib/websocket/connection.js` contains a disabled TODO stub. The
+`Sec-WebSocket-Extensions` request header is never sent.
+
+```js
+// lib/websocket/connection.js (v5.28.5)
+const permessageDeflate = '' // 'permessage-deflate; 15'
+// request.headersList.append('sec-websocket-extensions', permessageDeflate)
+```
+
+### Reason 3: Unsolicited extension responses are rejected
+
+If a server sends `Sec-WebSocket-Extensions: permessage-deflate` unprompted, the
+client detects the mismatch and calls `failWebsocketConnection()`.
+
+### Reason 4: No decompression logic in the receiver
+
+`lib/websocket/receiver.js` processes frames as raw bytes with no zlib usage.
+
+### Reason 5: Advisory semver ranges are imprecise
+
+The `< 6.24.0` bound captures v6.0.0–v6.23.x where the feature existed but was
+unpatched. It does not mean every version below 6.24.0 is vulnerable.
+
+---
+
+## CVE-2026-2229 Details
+
+In affected v6/v7 versions, `isValidClientWindowBits()` only checked for ASCII
+digits (allowing `"1000"`), and `createInflateRaw({ windowBits: 1000 })` threw an
+uncaught `RangeError` that crashed the process. Fixed in commit `cb79c570`.
+
+---
+
+## CVE-2026-1526 Details
+
+In affected v6/v7 versions, `PerMessageDeflate.decompress()` accumulated
+decompressed chunks without a size limit, enabling decompression-bomb DoS attacks
+via small compressed frames that expand to gigabytes in memory.
+
+---
+
+## Recommendation
+
+No remediation is required for undici v5.28.5 with respect to CVE-2026-1526 or
+CVE-2026-2229. Dismiss scanner findings with:
+
+> Both CVEs require permessage-deflate WebSocket compression (introduced in
+> undici v6.18.0). This feature does not exist in v5.28.5.
+
+Patched versions for v6/v7 users: **v6.24.0** and **v7.24.0**.
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+- [GHSA-vrm6-8vpv-qv8q (CVE-2026-1526)](https://github.com/nodejs/undici/security/advisories/GHSA-vrm6-8vpv-qv8q)
+- [GHSA-v9p9-hfj2-hcw8 (CVE-2026-2229)](https://github.com/nodejs/undici/security/advisories/GHSA-v9p9-hfj2-hcw8)
+- [Fix commit cb79c570](https://github.com/nodejs/undici/commit/cb79c5704ac47e42ce01a72269994fc70e377536)
+- [RFC 7692 — Compression Extensions for WebSocket](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7692)

